    What is selenium used for?
    Selenium helps maintain healthy thyroid function. Research shows, though, that too much can harm your thyroid. Cognitive support. Research shows selenium's antioxidant properties fight cell damage that may worsen brain and nervous system diseases like Parkinson's, Alzheimer's, and multiple sclerosis.२०२३ अगस्ट २१

    यसमार्फत खोज्नुहोस्: What is selenium used for?
    What does selenium to your body?
    Selenium is a constituent of 25 selenoproteins, including thioredoxin reductases, glutathione peroxidases, and selenoprotein P [1]. Selenoproteins play critical roles in thyroid hormone metabolism, DNA synthesis, reproduction, and protection from oxidative damage and infection [2-4].२०२४ अप्रिल १५

    यसमार्फत खोज्नुहोस्: What does selenium to your body?
    Is it safe to take selenium every day?
    It's typically not harmful to get some extra selenium in your diet, as long as you're not consuming more than 400 mcg a day (that's the Tolerable Upper Intake Level, or UL, which we'll get into momentarily). Just keep in mind that high levels of selenium can be dangerous, and it can also interact with some medications.२०२३ मे ३१
